Do you know the difference between gold filled vs gold plated? Most jewelry you buy is gold plated, meaning it has a layer of gold over materials such as brass, or sterling silver, that usually quite quickly fade and tarnish. Gold filled jewelry is the next best thing to solid gold at a fraction of the cost. Gold filled has 100x more gold than gold plated, and is long wear and tarnish resistant. You can shower with it, go swimming, and sweat in it without worrying about the gold fading. 
.
.
Anytime you look at investing in a jewelry piece, always be sure to check the quality of the metals! If you want long lasting items, always choose gold filled or solid gold.

Life is supposed to be lived in alignment with your truest and most authentic self 🤍 I felt out of alignment for so many years(and my body was telling me too)

TW: body image 
As a model(and a woman)  I’ve dealt w body image issues since I was 15. I cried at my first swimwear shoot because I didn’t feel thin enough- my brain was severely suffering from body dysmorphia. I would get anxiety every single swimwear shoot, or clothing shoot, worried I wouldn’t fit the clothes, that I wasn’t small enough. I remember a brand telling me they had to special order in a size *25* for me because the other girls are a 23/24 Jean. I am 5’10 and was already so small. I tried not to let it get to my head, and looking back I never realized how thin I truly was. Being a woman has meant that my body changes through hormones, through the ebbs and flows of life, and the hardest part of that is having my own internal expectation to be a certain size or I won’t be successful in my career. I won’t meet my own standard. The images I’ve shown are 3 weeks apart. I have gone thru massive personal trials and tribulations the past month, and sometimes it’s okay to not go to the gym everyday, or even take weeks off when needed. The real hardest part has been granting myself the patience and permission to just be okay where I’m at with my body, in my head. It’s hard to see pictures where I feel like I look bigger than I usually am. This post is for anyone dealing with body changes thru the ebbs and flows of life, and that I’m right there along with you and you’re not alone in this journey🫶🏼 it’s so refreshing to be open about something I’ve struggled with, that many models struggle with, that women in general struggle with. Each day I have focused my priority on being the healthiest I can be, fueling my body with good nutrition and Whole Foods, and listening to my body on what I need activity wise. Maybe it’s a walk, maybe it’s stretching or a HIIT class. Maybe it’s indulging sometimes. Just trying to live a balanced life and I feel proud of how far I’ve come, and all of the challenges I’ve overcome along the way. 🩵
